@NODE "BEEP" "BEEP"
Name:                 BEEP
Syntax:               BEEP
Description:          Simply causes InterSpread to beep or flash,
                      depending onwhat is currently selected in the
                      I/O-Screen sub-menu.
@ENDNODE
@node "CELL_MOVE" "CELL_MOVE"
Name:                 CELL_MOVE

Syntax:               CELL_MOVE <direction>

Description:          Moves the cell cursor one step in the direction
                      specified.

Parameters:           direction
                         The direction the cursor moves. Valid directions
                         are:
                         LEFT
                         RIGHT
                         UP
                         DOWN

Examples:             'CELL_MOVE' RIGHT   (Move one place to the right)
                      'CELL_MOVE' UP      (Move one place up)
@ENDNODE
@NODE "CURRENT_CELL" "CURRENT_CELL"

Name:                 CURRENT_CELL

Syntax:               CURRENT_CELL

Description:          Returns the name of the current cell as a string
                      (eg"C8","D12" etc).

Example:              'CURRENT_CELL' 
                      mystring = result

                      The string mystring now holds the name of the
                      current cell. 

See Also: @{"CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER" link "CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER"}, @{"CURRENT_SHEETPATH" link "CURRENT_SHEETPATH"}, @{"HOW_MANY_SHEETS" link "HOW_MANY_SHEETS"} 
@{"SHEETNAME" link "SHEETNAME"} @{"SHEETPATH" link "SHEETPATH"} 

@endnode

@node "CURRENT_SHEETNAME"

Name:                 CURRENT_SHEETNAME

Syntax:               CURRENT_SHEETNAME

Description:          Returns the name of the current sheet as a
                      string (eg"MySheet1").

Example:              'CURRENT_SHEETNAME'
                      mystring = result

                      The string mystring now holds the name of the
                      current sheet.

See Also: @{"CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER" link "CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER"}, @{"CURRENT_SHEETPATH" link "CURRENT_SHEETPATH"}, @{"HOW_MANY_SHEETS" link "HOW_MANY_SHEETS"} 
@{"SHEETNAME" link "SHEETNAME"}, @{"SHEETPATH" link "SHEETPATH"} 

@endnode

@node "CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER" "CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER"

Name                  CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER

Syntax                CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER

Description:          Returns the number of the current sheet.

Example:              'CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER'
                      myinteger = result

                      The variable myinteger now holds the current
                      sheet's number.

See Also: @{"CURRENT_SHEETNAME" link "CURRENT_SHEETNAME"}, @{"CURRENT_SHEETPATH" link "CURRENT_SHEETPATH"},  @{"HOW_MANY_SHEETS" link "HOW_MANY_SHEETS"},
@{"SHEETNAME" link "SHEETNAME"}, @{"SHEETPATH" link "SHEETPATH"}  

@endnode

@node "CURRENT_SHEETPATH" "CURRENT_SHEETPATH"

Name:                 CURRENT_SHEETPATH

Syntax:               CURRENT_SHEETPATH

Description:          Returns the full file pathname for the current
                      sheet as astring. (eg "InterSpread/Sheets/MySheet1")

Example:              'CURRENT_SHEETPATH'
                      mystring = result

                      The variable mystring now holds the current
                      sheet's path name. 

See Also: @{"CURRENT_SHEETNAME" link "CURRENT_SHEETNAME"}, @{"CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER" link "CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER"}, @{"HOW_MANY_SHEETS" link "HOW_MANY_SHEETS"} 
@{"SHEETNAME" link "SHEETNAME"} @{"SHEETPATH" link "SHEETPATH"} 

@endnode

@node "GET_CELL_RESULT" "GET_CELL_RESULT"

Name:                 GET_CELL_RESULT

Syntax:               GET_CELL_RESULT <cell>

Description:          Returns result of a RESULTLINE type of cell
                      (ie, a formulaor calculation cell). If the cell is
                      not a RESULTLINE cell, the command will fail and
                      interspread.lasterror will hold the error message.

Parameters:           cell
                         The coordinates of the cell you want to know
                         about. eg A4,E12, etc.

Examples:             'GET_CELL_RESULT' C2
                      'GET_CELL_RESULT' E14

See Also: @{"GET_CELL_VALUE" link "GET_CELL_VALUE"}

@endnode
@node "GET_CELL_TYPE" "GET_CELL_TYPE"

Name:                 GET_CELL_TYPE

Syntax:               GET_CELL_TYPE <cell>

Description:          Returns the cell type of the specified cell. It
                      returns one of the following:

                      RESULTLINE        A resultline cell
                      INTEGER           An integer cell
                      DECIMAL           A decimal cell
                      TEXTOVERFLOW      A text cell with overflow
                      FREE              An empty cell
                      TEXT              A text cell

Parameters:           cell
                         The coordinates of the cell whose type you want
                         to know. eg A4,E12, etc.	

Examples:             'GET_CELL_TYPE' A3
                      'GET_CELL_TYPE' D12

@endnode

@node "GET_CELL_VALUE" "GET_CELL_VALUE"

Name:                 GET_CELL_VALUE

Syntax:               GET_CELL_VALUE <cell>

Description:          Returns the value held in the specified cell
                      regardless ofthe cell's type.

Parameters:           cell
                         The coordinates of the cell whose value you
                         want to find out.eg A4, E12, etc.	

Examples:             'GET_CELL_VALUE' D4
                      'GET_CELL_VALUE' A16

See Also:	@{"GET_CELL_RESULT" link "GET_CELL_RESULT"}
@endnode

@node "GET_COLOR" "GET_COLOR"

Name:                 GET_COLOR

Syntax:               GET_COLOR <colour>

Description:          This returns the red, green and blue colour
                      values for the given colour register. These are
                      stored in the variable result and are given as a
                      string with spaces between each value. result will
                      hold something like "15 4 8", "0 3 12", etc.)

                      You may then use the ARexx parse command to split
                      these up into their separate components.

Parameters:           colour
                         The colour register that you want to know about.

Example:              'GET_COLOR' 4
                      PARSE VAR result rc gc bc

                      rc, gc, and bc now hold the red, green, and blue
                      values for colour register 4.

See Also: @{"SET_COLOR" link "SET_COLOR"}
@endnode

@node "HOW_MANY_SHEETS" "HOW_MANY_SHEETS"

Name:                 HOW_MANY_SHEETS

Syntax:               HOW_MANY_SHEETS

Description:          Returns the number of currently open sheets.

See Also: @{"CURRENT_SHEETNAME" link "CURRENT_SHEETNAME"}, @{"CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER" link "CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER"}, @{"CURRENT_SHEETPATH" link "CURRENT_SHEETPATH"},
@{"SHEETNAME" link "SHEETNAME"}, @{"SHEETPATH" link "SHEETPATH"}
@endnode

@node "INFO" "INFO"

Name:                 INFO

Syntax:               INFO '<text>'

Description:          Brings up an information requester displaying
                      the specified text. The requester disappears when
                      its Accept button is clicked.

Parameters:           text
                         The text to be displayed in the requester.

Example:              'INFO' 'My script has now finished'
		
See Also: @{"NUMREQ" link "NUMREQ"}, @{"SORRYREQ" link "SORRYREQ"}, @{"STRREQ" link "STRREQ"}
@endnode

@node "NUMREQ" "NUMREQ"

Name:                 NUMREQ

Syntax:               NUMREQ '<title>' '<text>' <sval> <width>

Description:          Displays a requester that allows you to request
                      a number from the user.

Parameters:           title
                         The text displayed in the title bar of the
                         requester.
                      text
                         The text displayed to the left of the number box.
                      sval
                         The suggested value in the box.
                      width
                         The width (in characters) of the box.

Example:              'NUMREQ' 'My Number Requester' 'Enter the meaning of
                      life : ' 

See Also: @{"INFO" link "INFO"}, @{"SORRYREQ" link "SORRYREQ"}, @{"STRREQ" link "STRREQ"}

@endnode

@node "SET_CELL_VALUE" "SET_CELL_VALUE"

Name:                 SET_CELL_VALUE

Syntax:               SET_CELL_VALUE <cell> <value>

Description:          Places the given value into the specified cell.

Parameters:           cell
                         The cell to be changed.
                      value
                         The value to place into it.

Examples:             'SET_CELL_VALUE' A12 27
                      'SET_CELL_VALUE' B6 hello

See Also: @{"SET_CURRENT_CELL_VALUE" link "SET_CURRENT_CELL_VALUE"}

@endnode

@node "SET_COLOR" "SET_COLOR"

Name:                 SET_COLOR

Syntax:               SET_COLOR <colour> <red> <green> <blue>

Description:          Changes a colour in the palette.

Parameters:           colour
                         The colour register to be changed
                      red
                         The red value       (0 to 15)
                      green
                         The green value     (0 to 15)
                      blue
                         The blue value      (0 to 15)

Examples:             'SET_COLOR' 1 15 15 15 (Set colour 1 to white)
                      'SET_COLOR' 2 0 0 0    (Set colour 2 to black)
                      'SET_COLOR' 3 15 0 0   (Set colour 3 to red)

See Also: @{"GET_COLOR" link "GET_COLOR"}

@endnode

@node "SET_CURRENT_CELL_VALUE" "SET_CURRENT_CELL_VALUE"

Name:                 SET_CURRENT_CELL_VALUE

Syntax:               SET_CURRENT_CELL_VALUE <value>

Description:          Places the given value into the current cell.

Parameters:           value
                         The value to give the cell.

Examples:             'SET_CURRENT_CELL_VALUE' 27
                      'SET_CURRENT_CELL_VALUE' hello

See Also: @{"SET_CELL_VALUE" link "SET_CELL_VALUE"}
@endnode

@node "SHEETNAME" "SHEETNAME"

Name:                 SHEETNAME

Syntax:               SHEETNAME <number>

Description:          Returns the name of a currently open sheet.

Parameters:           number
                         The number of the sheet whose name you want.

Example:              'SHEETNAME' 2

See Also: @{"CURRENT_SHEETNAME" link "CURRENT_SHEETNAME"}, @{"CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER" link "CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER"}, @{"CURRENT_SHEETPATH" link "CURRENT_SHEETPATH"},
@{"HOW_MANY_SHEETS" link "HOW_MANY_SHEETS"}, @{"SHEETPATH" link "SHEETPATH"}

@endnode
@node "SHEETPATH" "SHEETPATH"

Name:                 SHEETPATH

Syntax:               SHEETPATH <number>

Description:          Returns the full file pathname of a currently
                      open sheet.

Parameters:           number
                         The number of the sheet whose path name you want
                         to find out.

See Also:  @{"CURRENT_SHEETNAME" link "CURRENT_SHEETNAME"}, @{"CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER" link "CURRENT_SHEETNUMBER"}, @{"CURRENT_SHEETPATH" link "CURRENT_SHEETPATH"},
@{"HOW_MANY_SHEETS" link "HOW_MANY_SHEETS"}, @{"SHEETNAME" link "SHEETNAME"}

@endnode

@node "SORRYREQ" "SORRYREQ"

Name:                 SORRYREQ

Syntax:               SORRYREQ '<text>'

Description:          Brings up a 'Sorry' requester displaying the
                      specified text. The requester disappears when the
                      user clicks the Accept button.

Parameters:           text
                         The text to be displayed in the requester.

Example:              'SORRYREQ' 'I can't find your file!'

See Also: @{"INFO" link "INFO"}, @{"NUMREQ" link "NUMREQ"}, @{"STRREQ" link "STRREQ"}

@endnode

@node "STRREQ" "STRREQ"

Name:                 STRREQ

Syntax:               STRREQ '<title>' '<text>' <width>

Description:          Displays a requester allowing you to request text
                      input from the user.

Parameters:           title
                         The text displayed in the requester's title bar.
                      text
                         The text displayed to the left of the string box.
                      width
                         The width (in characters) of the box.

Example:              'NUMREQ' 'My Number Requester' 'Enter your name : '
                      12

See Also: @{"INFO" link "INFO"}, @{"NUMREQ" link "NUMREQ"}, @{"SORRYREQ" link "SORRYREQ"}

@endnode

@node "NEW_SHEET" "NEW_SHEET"

Name:                 NEW_SHEET

Syntax:               NEW_SHEET

Description:          Creates a blank new sheet.

@endnode

@node "OPEN_SHEET" "OPEN_SHEET"

Name:                 OPEN_SHEET

Syntax:               OPEN_SHEET '<pathname>'

Description:          Loads a sheet from disk or RAM. 

Parameters:           pathname

                      The full file pathname of the sheet to load. If
                      no pathname is specified,the file requester is
                      brought up.

Example:              'OPEN_SHEET' 'InterSpread:Sheets/Mysheet1'

@endnode

@node "CLOSE_SHEET" "CLOSE_SHEET"

Name:                 CLOSE_SHEET

Syntax:               CLOSE_SHEET

Description:          Closes the current sheet.

@endnode

@node "ARCHIVE_SHEET" "ARCHIVE_SHEET"

Name:                 ARCHIVE_SHEET

Syntax:               ARCHIVE_SHEET

Description:          Saves the current sheet using the file name under
                      which it was loaded or last saved. If the sheet has
                      not yet been named, the 'SaveSheet' requester will
                      be brought up.

@endnode

@node "ARCHIVE_SHEET_AS" "ARCHIVE_SHEET_AS"

Name:                 ARCHIVE_SHEET_AS

Syntax:               ARCHIVE_SHEET_AS '<pathname>'

Description:          Saves the current sheet to disk using the given
                      file and path names.

Parameters:           pathname
                         The full file path name to save the sheet under.
                         If no pathname is specified, the file requester
                         is brought up.

Example:              'ARCHIVE_SHEET_AS' 'InterSpread:Sheets/Mysheet1'

@endnode

@node "PRINT" "PRINT"

Name:                 PRINT

Syntax:               PRINT [NOW]

Description:          Prints the current sheet.

Parameters:           When NOW is specified, the sheet is printed
                      immediately with the current print settings,
                      otherwise the print requester is brought up.

@endnode

@node "CHOOSE_SHEET" "CHOOSE_SHEET"

Name:                 CHOOSE_SHEET

Syntax:               CHOOSE_SHEET <number>

Description:          Selects and activates the specified sheet.

Parameters:           number
                         The number of the sheet to open. If no number is
                         specified, the user is prompted with the sheet
                         select requester to select one manually.

Examples:             'CHOOSE_SHEET' 4
                      'CHOOSE_SHEET' 

@endnode

@node "DISK_OPERATIONS" "DISK_OPERATIONS"

Name:                 DISK_OPERATIONS

Syntax:               DISK_OPERATIONS

Description:          Brings up the disk operations requester. If the
                      user loadsa sheet, the full file pathname is
                      returned in result.

@endnode

@node "PRESET_SAVE" "PRESET_SAVE"

Name:                 PRESET_SAVE

Syntax:               PRESET_SAVE

Description:          Save the current preferences to disk so that they
                      becomethe new defaults.

@endnode

@node "ABOUT" "ABOUT"

Name:                 ABOUT

Syntax:               ABOUT

Description:          Brings up About requester.

@endnode

@node "QUIT" "QUIT"

Name:                 QUIT

Syntax:               QUIT

Description:          Quits InterSpread.
@endnode

@node "CUT" "CUT"

Name:                 CUT

Syntax:               CUT

Description:          Cuts the defined block, and stores it in the Clipboard.

@endnode

@node "COPY" "COPY"

Name:                 COPY

Syntax:               COPY

Description:          Copies the defined block to the Clipboard.

@endnode

@node "PASTE" "PASTE"

Name:                 PASTE

Syntax:               PASTE

Description:          Inserts the contents of the Clipboard at the
                      location of the cell cursor.
@endnode

@node "ERASE" "ERASE"

Name:                 ERASE

Syntax:               ERASE

Description:          Delete the defined block.

@endnode

@node "CUT_ONLY_DATA" "CUT_ONLY_DATA"

Name:                 CUT_ONLY_DATA

Syntax:               CUT_ONLY_DATA

Description:          Cuts and stores only the pure data from the
                      defined block (ie, without cell settings) in
                      the Clipboard.
@endnode

@node "COPY_ONLY_DATA" "COPY_ONLY_DATA"

Name:                 COPY_ONLY_DATA

Syntax:               COPY_ONLY_DATA

Description:          Stores only the pure data from the defined block
                      (ie, without cell settings) in the Clipboard.
@endnode

@node "SELECT_BLOCK" "SELECT_BLOCK"

Name:                 SELECT_BLOCK

Syntax:               SELECT_BLOCK <topleft> <bottomright>

Description:          Selects a block of cells.

Parameters:           topleft
                         The cell to the top left of the block you wish
                         to select.
                      bottomright
                         The cell to the bottom right of the block you wish
                         to select.

                      If no parameters are included, the block selection
                      requester will be brought up.

Examples:             'SELECT_BLOCK'
                      'SELECT_BLOCK' A2 E6

@endnode

@node "CURRENCY" "CURRENCY"

Name:                 CURRENCY

Syntax:               CURRENCY <number>

Description:          Select currency.

Parameters:           number
                         This holds a number between 0 and 16 which
                         corresponds to the menu item referred to in
                         the Currency sub-menu which by default, holds
                         the following:
                         0   No Currency
                         1   :	%
                         2   KR  :
                         3   KR  : ,-
                         4   $   :
                         5   :
                         6   :   m/s
                         7   :   m/s^2
                         8   :   m/s^3
                         9   :   m^2
                         10  :   m^3
                         11  :   m
                         12  :   Kg
                         13  :   g
                         14  :   Hz
                         15  :   atm
                         16  :   cal

Examples:                'CURRENCY' 4  (Set currency to $)
                         'CURRENCY' 14 (Set currency to Hz)

@endnode

@node "DECIMALS_OPTIMIZE" "DECIMALS_OPTIMIZE"

Name:                 DECIMALS_OPTIMIZE

Syntax:               DECIMALS_OPTIMIZE

Description:          Optimize the number of decimal places for the
                      selected cell or block.

@endnode

@node "DECIMALS_SPECIFY" "DECIMALS_SPECIFY"

Name:                 DECIMALS_SPECIFY

Syntax:               DECIMALS_SPECIFY <number>

Description:          Specify the number of decimals for the selected
                      cell or block.

Parameters:           number
                         The number of decimal places.

Example:              'DECIMALS_SPECIFY' 2

@endnode

@node "FORMATS_STANDARD" "FORMATS_STANDARD"

Name:                 FORMATS_STANDARD

Syntax:               FORMATS_STANDARD

Description:          Use standard cell format for the selected cell
                      or block.

@endnode

@node "FORMATS_SCIENTIFIC" "FORMATS_SCIENTIFIC"

Name:                 FORMATS_SCIENTIFIC

Syntax:               FORMATS_SCIENTIFIC

Description:          Use scientific notation for the selected cell or block.

@endnode

@node "FORMATS_COMMAS" "FORMATS_COMMAS"

Name:                 FORMATS_COMMAS

Syntax:               FORMATS_COMMAS

Description:          If you choose not to use Scientific notation, and
                      are working with large numbers, this option will
                      insert commas every third figure to the right of
                      the decimal point to make reading the numbers easier.

@endnode

@node "COLUMN_WIDTH_STANDARD" "COLUMN_WIDTH_STANDARD"

Name:                 COLUMN_WIDTH_STANDARD

Syntax:               COLUMN_WIDTH_STANDARD

Description:          Set the current column to the standard cell
                      width (nine characters unless a new standard is
                      defined).

@endnode

@node "COLUMN_WIDTH_DOUBLE" "COLUMN_WIDTH_DOUBLE"

Name:                 COLUMN_WIDTH_DOUBLE

Syntax:               COLUMN_WIDTH_DOUBLE

Description:          Sets the current column width to 18 characters.

@endnode

@node "COLUMN_WIDTH_SET" "COLUMN_WIDTH_SET"

Name:                 COLUMN_WIDTH_SET

Syntax:               COLUMN_WIDTH_SET <width>

Description:          Sets the current column to the specified cell width.

Parameters:           width
                         The width in characters to set the column.

Example:              'COLUMN_WIDTH_SET' 16

@endnode

@node "COLUMN_WIDTH_SET_STANDARD" "COLUMN_WIDTH_SET_STANDARD"

Name:                 COLUMN_WIDTH_SET_STANDARD

Syntax:               COLUMN_WIDTH_SET_STANDARD <width>

Description:          Sets the default column width.

Parameters:           width
                         The number of characters to change the default
                         width to.

Example:              'COLUMN_WIDTH_SET_STANDARD' 6

@endnode

@node "STYLE" "STYLE"

Name:                 STYLE

Syntax:               STYLE '<styletype>'

Description:          Set the style for the selected cell or block.

Parameters:           styletype
                         Can be one of the following :
                         NORMAL
                         ITALIC
                         BOLD
                         UNDERLINE
                         SUPERSCRIPT
                         SUBSCRIPT
                         COLOR1
                         COLOR2
                         COLOR3
		
Examples:             'STYLE' 'BOLD'    (Set style to bold)
                      'STYLE' 'COLOR1'  (Set text colour to register 1)

@endnode

@node "INDENT" "INDENT"

Name:                 INDENT

Syntax:               INDENT '<indenttype>'

Description:          Set the indent type for the selected cell or block.

Parameters:           indenttype
                         Can be one of the following:

                         NATURAL
                         RIGHT
                         LEFT
                         CENTERED

Examples:             'INDENT' 'RIGHT'  (Right justify cell/block)
                      'INDENT' 'CENTRE' (Centre justify cell/block)

@endnode

@node "PROTECT_CELL" "PROTECT_CELL"

Name:                 PROTECT_CELL

Syntax:               PROTECT_CELL

Description:          Protects the selected cell or block.

@endnode

@node "LOCK_TITLES" "LOCK_TITLES"

Name:                 LOCK_TITLES

Syntax:               LOCK_TITLES '<locktype>'

Description:          Locks rows or columns.

Parameters:           locktype
                         Can be one of the following:
                         UNLOCKED
                         VERTICAL
                         HORIZONTAL
                         BOTH

Examples:             'LOCK_TITLES' 'VERTICAL'  (Locks selected columns)
                      'LOCK_TITLES' 'UNLOCKED'  (Unlocks previously locked
                                                              rows/columns)

@endnode

@node "FILL_RIGHT" "FILL_RIGHT"

Name:                 FILL_RIGHT

Syntax:               FILL_RIGHT

Description:          Copies the data in the left-hand column of cells
                      in a block to all selected cells to its right.
@endnode

@node "FILL_DOWN" "FILL_DOWN"

Name:                 FILL_DOWN

Syntax:               FILL_DOWN

Description:          Copies the data in the top row of a block of cells
                      to all selected cells underneath it.

@endnode

@node "ERASE_COLUMNS" "ERASE_COLUMNS"

Name:                 ERASE_COLUMNS

Syntax:               ERASE_COLUMNS <number>

Description:          Erase the specified number of columns to the
                      right from the current cursor position.

Parameters:           number 
                         The number of columns to erase.

Example:              'ERASE_COLUMNS' 3  (Erases 3 columns)

@endnode

@node "ERASE_ROWS" "ERASE_ROWS"

Name:                 ERASE_ROWS

Syntax:               ERASE_ROWS <number>

Description:          Erase the specified number of row downwards
                      from the current cursor position.

Parameters:           number
                         The number of rows to erase.

Example:              'ERASE_ROWS' 4  (Erases 4 rows)

@endnode

@node "INSERT_COLUMNS" "INSERT_COLUMNS"

Name:                 INSERT_COLUMNS

Syntax:               INSERT_COLUMNS <number>

Description:          Inserts the specified number of columns at the
                      current cursor position.

Parameters:           number
                         The number of columns to insert

Example:              'INSERT_COLUMNS' 2  (Inserts 2 columns)

@endnode

@node "INSERT_ROWS" "INSERT_ROWS"

Name:                 INSERT_ROWS

Syntax:               INSERT_ROWS <number>

Description:          Inserts the specified number of rows at the
                      current cursor position.

Parameters:           number
                         The number of rows to insert.

Example:              'INSERT_ROWS' 1  (Inserts 1 row)

@endnode

@node "GOTO_CELL" "GOTO_CELL"

Name:                 GOTO_CELL

Syntax:               GOTO_CELL <cell>

Description:          Moves the cell cursor to the specified cell.

Parameters:           cell
                         The reference to the cell position you want to
                         go to (eg A4, E12).

@endnode


@node "MENU" "MENU"

Name:                 MENU

Syntax:               MENU <menu> <item> <sub>

Description:          Allows you to directly access any menu command. 

                      NB. This command is not recommended for general
                      use as your ARexx scripts may not be compatible
                      with future versions of InterSpread Pro. Use
                      MENU only when there is no other specific ARexx
                      command to perform the same action.

Parameters:           menu
                         The menu number
                      item
                         The item number
                      sub
                         The sub-menu item number

Overview:

There now follows a list of all menu numbers for use with the MENU 
command.'(Divider)' is a horizontal line divider in a menu. Specifying
these menu items in the MENU command does nothing.

Project menu 

Menu No:   Item No:   Submenu No:   Command Name:

   0          0          0             New Sheet
   0          1          0             Open Sheet
   0          2          0             (divider)
   0          3          0             Close Sheet
   0          4          0             Save
   0          5          0             Save as...
   0          6          0             (divider)
   0          7          0             Print
   0          8          0             Choose Sheet
   0          9          0             Disk Operations
   0          1          0             (divider)
   0          1          0             Save Preferences
   0          1          0             About
   0          1          0             Quit

Edit Menu 

Menu No:   Item No:   Submenu No:   Command Name:

   1          0          0             Cut
   1          1          0             Copy
   1          2          0             Paste
   1          3          0             (divider)
   1          4          0             Erase
   1          5          0             (divider)
   1          6          0             Cut only data
   1          7          0             Copy only data
   1          8          0             (divider)
   1          9          0             Select Block

Cell Menu 

Menu No:   Item No:   Submenu No:   Command Name:

   2          0          0             No currency
   2          0          1-15          Misc currencies
   2          0          16             Redefine currency
   2          1          0             Number of decimals - Optimize
   2          1          1             Number of decimals - Specify
   2          2          0             Formats - Standard
   2          2          1             Formats - Scientific notation
   2          2          2             Formats - Commas
   2          2          3             (divider)
   2          2          4             Formats - Date (DAY-MTH-YEAR)
   2          2          5             Formats - Date (DAY-MTH)
   2          2          6             Formats - Date (MTH-YEAR)
   2          2          7             (divider)
   2          2          8             Formats - Time (HH:MM)
   2          2          9             Formats - 24 Hour Clock
   2          2          10            Formats - Timeprefix...
   2          3          0             Column Width - Standard
   2          3          1             Column Width - Double
   2          3          2             Column Width - Specify...
   2          3          3             Column Width - Set Standard...
   2          4          0             Style - Normal
   2          4          1             Style - Italic
   2          4          2             Style - Bold
   2          4          3             Style - Underline
   2          4          4             Style - Superscript
   2          4          5             Style - Subscript
   2          4          6             Style - Color 1
   2          4          7             Style - Color 2
   2          4          8             Style - Color 3
   2          5          0             Indent - Normal
   2          5          1             Indent - Right
   2          5          2             Indent - Left
   2          5          3             Indent - Centered
   2          6          0             Protect Cell
   2          7          0             Cell Password
   2          8          0             Define Cell Password

Sheet Menu 

Menu No:   Item No:   Submenu No:   Command Name:

   3          0          0             Lock Titles
   3          1          0             RETURN/ENTER
   3          2          0             Show - Cellcontent in Inputline
   3          2          1             Show - Formulas instead of Facit
   3          3          0             Input in Cell
   3          4          0             Comma as Decimalpoint

Functions Menu

Menu No:   Item No:   Submenu No:   Command Name:

   4          0          0             Fill Right
   4          1          0             Fill Down
   4          2          0             Erase Column(s)
   4          2          1             Erase Row(s)
   4          3          0             Insert Column(s)
   4          3          1             Insert Row(s)
   4          4          0             Protect Text
   4          5          0             Protect Formulas
   4          6          0             Move to Cell
   4          7          0             Sort Data - Ascending
   4          7          1             Sort Data - Descending
   4          8          0             Cellnote
   4          9          0             Find Data

Calculation Menu 

Menu No:   Item No:   Submenu No:   Command Name:

   5          0          0             Convert to number
   5          1          0             Freeze References
   5          2          0             Insert Sheetname
   5          3          0             Define Blockname
   5          4          0             Insert Blockname
   5          5          0             Erase Blockname
   5          6          0             Insert Function
   5          7          0             Calculation Order - Natural
   5          7          1             Calculation Order - Row by Row
   5          7          2             Calculation Order - Column by Column
   5          8          0             Calculation Update - Automatic
   5          8          1             Calculation Update - Manual
   5          8          2             Calculation Update - Now!

I/O Menu 

Menu No:   Item No:   Submenu No:   Command Name:

   6          0          0             InterWord to Front
   6          1          0             Transfer to InterWord
   6          2          0             Transfer Data to InterWord
   6          3          0             Close Workbench
   6          4          0             Screen - Color
   6          4          1             Screen - Interlace
   6          4          2             Screen - 9 Pixel
   6          4          3             Screen - Grid
   6          4          4             Screen - Palette
   6          4          5             Screen - Flash

Chart Menu 

Menu No:   Item No:   Submenu No:   Command Name:

   7          0          0             Draw Chart - 1
   7          0          1             Draw Chart - 2
